<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910530-0019</DOCNO><DOCID>910530-0019.</DOCID><HL>   Marketing Brief -- Hearst Corp.:   Publisher to Move 250 Jobs   To North Carolina Facility</HL><DATE>05/30/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7</SO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)</IN><RE>NORTH CAROLINA (NC)NEW YORK (NY)</RE><LP>   Hearst Corp. said it will move about 250 staff jobs out ofNew York to a new facility in Charlotte, N.C.   A company spokesman said Hearst would be moving peoplefrom its corporate staff and Hearst Magazines division. Themove will affect staff in accounting, purchasing and dataprocessing areas. The spokesman said there are no plans forHearst Corp., which publishes books, newspapers, magazines,and owns cable TV interests, to move from New York.</LP><TEXT>   The move will affect 10% of the company's New York staffof 2,400. Hearst is acting to cut costs after the companygrew quickly in the 1980s following several largeacquisitions. The move, which will take about 18 months, willbegin in the fall.</TEXT></DOC>